status: MARC21-007: Emulsion on film of microform
Type of light-sensitive material on the film.

definition (en): A compound of silver and halogens.

Sensitized layers composed of diazonium salts that react with couplers to form dye images. The color of the image is determined by the composition of the diazonium compound as well as the couplers used in the process.

Light-sensitive component is suspended in a plastic layer. On exposure, the component creates optical vesicules (bubbles) in the layers. These bubbles form the latent image. The latent image becomes visible and fixed by heating the plastic layer and then allowing it to cool.

scope note (en): For example, a microfilm may have slices of film with one type of emulsion and other slices with another type of emulsion.

definition (en): Item does not have emulsion on film.
Emulsion on the film is not known.
Emulsion on film other than silver halide, diazo, vesicular, mixed emulsion.
